OL,5,CBurn-in                                
OL,6, OLED and Plasma TVs are suspectible to 
OL,7, permanent burn-in from static images.  
OL,8, On these display types, it's worth     
OL,9, checking if this has been mitigated,   
OL,10, for example by not driving pixels at   
OL,11, full intensity or use of the pixel     
OL,12, orbiter.                               
OL,14, When reviewing OLED/Plasma sets, please
OL,15, include whether or not any burn-in     
OL,16, reduction features work when using     
OL,17, teletext.                              
OL,19, On OLEDs withARBGDBGW subpixels, red is
OL,20, the most suspectible colour. Fortunate-
OL,21, ly, red is used infrequently, but watch
OL,22, out for yellow headings and red Fastext
OL,23, links!                                 
