OL,5,CPage memory                            
OL,6, Most modern TVs can cache hundreds of  
OL,7, pages in the background, enabling fast 
OL,8, access to almost any page. Older sets  
OL,9, usually only have enough memory for the
OL,10, currently displayed page and no more,  
OL,11, meaning you have to wait for the next  
OL,12, page to be re-transmitted before you   
OL,13, can see it; purists will want this.    
OL,14, Some old sets can hold 7 or 8 pages.   
OL,15, A lower limit may apply to the number  
OL,16, of subpages that can be stored for one 
OL,17, page; P521 makes good test material.   
OL,19,CSubpage handling                       
OL,20, TEEFAX uses a lot of subpages. Ease of 
OL,21, subpage selection is important for the 
OL,22, best experience.                       
